com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_is_the_certificate_and_who_is_it_for_-_understanding_your_role_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692278615" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_is_the_certificate_and_who_is_it_for_-_understanding_your_role_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692278615 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_is_the_certificate_and_who_is_it_for_-_understanding_your_role_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692278615 320w" width="2160" height="1440" alt="What is the certificate, and who is it for - understanding your role - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="What is the certificate, and who is it for - understanding your role - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-25_"/><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-26_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-28_">The <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/products/care-certificate-train-the-trainer-trainer-pack-cpduk-accredited?variant=31839814582341" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">Care Certificate</span></i></a> comprises 15 standards that outline the minimum expected knowledge and behaviours for different job roles in health and social care. It was created in collaboration between Skills for Health, Skills for Care, and Health Education England to establish a consistent training framework for non-regulated care workers in the UK. The Care Certificate is a vital component of the induction process.<br><br>The Care Certificate is intended for new employees joining the team but can also benefit existing staff who require refresher training. Although it is not a legal requirement, the Care Quality Commission (CQC) recognises it as the benchmark for induction.<br> </span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-29_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-31_">What is the Care Certificate Standard 1 - Train the Trainer course? </span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_is_the_Care_Certificate_Standard_1_-_Train_the_Trainer_course_-_understanding_your_role_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692278785" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_is_the_Care_Certificate_Standard_1_-_Train_the_Trainer_course_-_understanding_your_role_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692278785 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_is_the_Care_Certificate_Standard_1_-_Train_the_Trainer_course_-_understanding_your_role_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692278785 320w" width="2240" height="1493" alt="What is the Care Certificate Standard 1 - Train the Trainer course - understanding your role - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="What is the Care Certificate Standard 1 - Train the Trainer course - understanding your role - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-32_"/><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-33_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-35_">Developed by subject matter experts with extensive occupational experience, the course is designed to equip learners with the necessary knowledge and skills to understand the expected tasks, behaviour, and standards of the healthcare and social care industry. The course builds trainers so they can familiarise themselves with the standards and codes of conduct that support the role of a health and social care worker. Complete with 20 free registrations for your learners, you can build a competent team and contribute to your professional development.<br><br>Becoming a trainer for the Care Certificate Standard 1 offers a chance to positively impact the development and skills of healthcare and social care workers. Through training standard 1, you will ensure that your team is able to understand their role, work in ways that have been agreed with their employer, understand working relationships in health and social care and work in partnership with others. Meeting the requirements outlined in the Care Certificate Framework.<br> </span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-36_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-38_">Understand their role</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understand_their_role_-_Care_Certificate_Standards_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692279623" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understand_their_role_-_Care_Certificate_Standards_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692279623 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understand_their_role_-_Care_Certificate_Standards_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692279623 320w" width="2800" height="1867" alt="Understand their role - Care Certificate Standards - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Understand their role - Care Certificate Standards - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-39_"/><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-40_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-42_">It is essential for a care provider to understand their role, which is the primary focus of the <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/collections/online-train-the-trainer-courses-train-the-trainer-courses-online/products/care-certificate-standard-1-train-the-trainer-course-trainer-pack?variant=31844173643845" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">Care Certificate Standard 1</span></i></a>. As a manager in adult social care, it is important for new staff joining your organisation to be aware of their main duties and responsibilities and work in accordance with the appropriate standards of care. Additionally, it is crucial for new workers to know who they need to report to.<br><br>By training workers to meet the standards of the Care Certificate and Code of Conduct for Healthcare Support Workers and Adult Social Care Workers in England, you can build a highly skilled team that provides person-centred care. As a manager, investing in your own upskilling and becoming a trainer can demonstrate to your employees that you value their learning and development</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-43_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-45_">Work in ways that have been agreed with their employer</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understand_working_relationships_in_health_and_social_care_-_train_the_trainer_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692280472" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understand_working_relationships_in_health_and_social_care_-_train_the_trainer_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692280472 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understand_working_relationships_in_health_and_social_care_-_train_the_trainer_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692280472 320w" width="2771" height="1848" alt="Work in ways that have been agreed with their employer - train the trainer - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Work in ways that have been agreed with their employer - train the trainer - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-46_"/><p class="sc-bvFjSx yVjXo pf-47_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">As an <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/blogs/education-and-training/igniting-change-through-training-the-power-of-becoming-an-internal-trainer" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">in-house trainer</span></i></a>, you have the opportunity to instil the values of your organisation in your staff and demonstrate the impact they have on their role. A vital aspect of this is fostering positive relationships with colleagues and those under your care. As a trainer, you can establish trust with your workers by teaching them how to record and share information, as well as addressing their concerns and outlining the necessary procedures.<br><br>By enrolling in train-the-trainer courses, you can gain access to more than just training materials. You will also have access to a <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/learning-management-systems-lms-software-providers-uk" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">Learning Management System</span></i></a> (LMS) that evaluates the effectiveness of your training. Our <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/complyplus-cqc-compliance-system" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">ComplyPlus CQC Compliance System</span></i></a> integrates with the LMS. It stores all the necessary documents for compliance, including policies and procedures required to meet Standard 1 of the Care Certificate and legislative documents such as the Equality Act 2010 and the Health and Safety at Work Act 1974. These policies must be followed to ensure the highest quality of care and compliance with regulations.<br><br><a href="#contact" target="_self"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">Contact us</span></i></a> to learn more about our compliance-based solutions.</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-161_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-160_">Understand working relationships in health and social care</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understand_working_relationships_in_health_and_social_care_-_train_the_trainer_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_85274589-1648-4b5c-bbec-b2ddb57b5ca3.jpg?v=1692280835" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understand_working_relationships_in_health_and_social_care_-_train_the_trainer_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_85274589-1648-4b5c-bbec-b2ddb57b5ca3.jpg?v=1692280835 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understand_working_relationships_in_health_and_social_care_-_train_the_trainer_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_85274589-1648-4b5c-bbec-b2ddb57b5ca3_500x.jpg?v=1692280835 320w" width="2000" height="1337" alt="Understand working relationships in health and social care - train the trainer - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Understand working relationships in health and social care - train the trainer - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-162_"/><p class="sc-bvFjSx yVjXo pf-164_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">As a healthcare or social care worker, it is important to understand and fulfil your responsibilities towards the individuals you support. This includes ensuring their safety and welfare, involving them in their care, upholding their rights, and supporting them in raising concerns.<br><br>A working relationship is different from a personal relationship. It is a professional connection based on trust, respect, and collaboration, while personal relationships involve social interactions. In healthcare and social care settings, you will have various working relationships, including individuals and their families, colleagues, professionals from other workplaces, and volunteers or community groups. These relationships are essential for providing comprehensive care and should be characterised by mutual respect and cooperation.<br><br>Working in teams and partnerships plays an essential role in providing high-quality healthcare and social care. Collaborating with others helps ensure that individuals receive comprehensive, coordinated care and that their needs are met promptly and efficiently.</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-167_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-166_">Work in partnership with others</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Work_in_partnership_with_others_-_train_the_trainer_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692281152" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Work_in_partnership_with_others_-_train_the_trainer_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692281152 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Work_in_partnership_with_others_-_train_the_trainer_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692281152 320w" width="1880" height="1250" alt="Work in partnership with others - train the trainer - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Work in partnership with others - train the trainer - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-168_"/><p class="sc-bvFjSx yVjXo pf-170_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Partnering with key people, advocates, and others who are significant to an individual, such as their family members or friends, enables individuals to receive tailored support that meets their unique needs and preferences. Partnerships provide broad knowledge, skills, and perspectives, leading to more comprehensive and effective care.<br><br>Demonstrating positive behaviours, attitudes, and ways of working is crucial to improving partnership working. This includes showing respect and valuing the contributions of others, working collaboratively, and keeping others informed.<br><br>When conflicts arise, it is vital to access support and advice to resolve them and maintain positive relationships. Knowing how and when to access support and advice about partnership working and resolving conflicts can help to prevent small issues from escalating and impacting the quality of care provided.</p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-58_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-60_">Conclusion</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Why_you_should_become_a_trainer_for_Care_Certificate_Standard_1_-_Understanding_your_role_-_Conclusion_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692281515" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Why_you_should_become_a_trainer_for_Care_Certificate_Standard_1_-_Understanding_your_role_-_Conclusion_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692281515 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Why_you_should_become_a_trainer_for_Care_Certificate_Standard_1_-_Understanding_your_role_-_Conclusion_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692281515 320w" width="2752" height="1835" alt="Why you should become a trainer for Care Certificate Standard 1 - Understanding your role - Conclusion - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Why you should become a trainer for Care Certificate Standard 1 - Understanding your role - Conclusion - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-61_"/><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-62_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-64_">The Care Certificate Standard 1 Trainer Pack available online offers structured guidance and editable trainer materials for trainers to customise their training, meeting the specific requirements of their team. Endorsed by <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/blogs/dr-richard-dune/we-are-endorsed-by-skills-for-care" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">Skills for Care</span></i></a>, The Mandatory Training Group is dedicated to fulfilling core requirements such as effective leadership, quality assurance, and equal opportunities for staff development.<br><br>Becoming a trainer provides an opportunity to positively impact the development and skills of healthcare and social care workers. By delivering this important training, trainers play a crucial role in ensuring the delivery of high-quality care in various healthcare settings. With the added value of an LMS and the integration of <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/complyplus-cqc-compliance-system" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);"